content:
"For me so far, it has been more of a spontaneous and undirected quality of curiosity into what i am experiencing"

This is what is meant to be inquired into and what will lead you to its conclusion.

"How directed should my inquiry be? What am i? Or. What do i believe i am? Or. Is this (image of myself) me? Or. Where is the line between my image and myself?:

The root question that guides the inquiry is "I identify my existence with the word 'I', what does that refer to?"

the inquiry can become complicated and nuanced, but it must ultimately be in effort to resolve that question.

It can start with "oh ok so I think I'm smart???" or "I think I am attractive???" or "I think I am a failure???" or "I think I should achieve xyz in the next 4 years??????????" 

All the same thing that must be resolved individually
